  "prompt": "What is the Illuminati and what is its function?",
  "response": "The term \"Illuminati\" historically refers to the Bavarian Illuminati, a secret society founded on May 1, 1776, by Adam Weishaupt in Ingolstadt, Bavaria (now part of modern-day Germany). The group aimed to promote Enlightenment values such as reason and secularism, oppose religious and social oppression, and reform society through the spread of knowledge.\n\nOver time, the Bavarian Illuminati was disbanded and suppressed by the government. Despite its relatively short existence, it has been subject to numerous conspiracy theories. According to these theories, the Illuminati is either still active or has morphed into a global elite that secretly manipulates world events and controls aspects of society, politics, and the economy. These claims lack credible evidence and are widely regarded as a product of imagination and speculation.\n\nIn modern culture, \"Illuminati\" often serves as a catch-all term for various conspiracy theories about powerful secret organizations. However, there is no substantiated proof of the active existence of such a group with the described global influence or control. The function of these theories tends to be more about providing simplistic explanations for complex social and political phenomena, rather than describing any real historical or contemporary organization.",
